name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @danielmeigs @elonmusk Would need additional features added too like notifications that a Tweet you re-tweeted was edited. The social implications of a RT are complicated. I wouldn't want to RT something knowing it could say something different in a few min.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @danielmeigs @elonmusk Even if you had that, the way Tweets spread and the way they're used, you'd still need a way to know if a Tweet was edited and what was edited, and given how they spread via screenshots or are shown on news, you'd have to make clear that it's edited visually to avoid abuse.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @elonmusk Only if it's time limited, you can see the full history of edits publicly, and you couldn't take a screenshot of a Tweet or view it at all without an incredibly clear way of telling that it was edited via format/color or something, a badge you can't crop out, etc. Very important.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @chriswbrashear @DJJenkins @Twitter Also, all edits should be viewable. Iterations available. The less limitations the easier it should be to see that the Tweet (without digging) was edited, and what was edited.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @chriswbrashear @DJJenkins @Twitter Yup lots of room for problems. That's why I think they haven't done it. It's a big tree of "yea but what if" issues that get ugly fast.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Again, these Tweets are self-reflective. I've caught myself twice in the last week (probably more) sending a text or email to someone before going "wait, did I even bother looking??" only to find what I needed right away. What a goofball.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @DJJenkins @Twitter I'm only for it if it had a time limit on it, like under 60 seconds w/possible extra layer of limitations on just HOW different the Tweet can be, which should satisfy some of the "ugh typo!" situations but not allow the sort of abuse everyone's warned about, which I agree with.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Giving up is an option too. You don't have to know everything, you just need to prioritize what's worth knowing, and start the process.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: If you don't know, ask. If you don't know, look. If you don't know, think. If you don't know, observe. If you don't know, search. If you don't know, read. If you don't know, try. If you don't know, test. If you still don't know, do everything over again until you do. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

tweet: So basically they leave you with no choice but to pay to file 4x per yr despite it being largely unnecessary, so you end up paying in tax prep & filing what you'd likely pay in penalties to not file 4x & wait till years end, a cashflow squeeze for small biz but comfy for them.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Another fav of mine is the penalties you get hit with for not (essentially) pre-paying your taxes blind. If you don't pay to have quarterly filings done/paid, you have to send est. payments, otherwise face gross penalties for not sending, yet if you're short, there's interest.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: IRS understaffed as well. 2021 it took 6+mo for piece of paperwork on name change confirmation that had been sent 4+yrs ago to be resent by me & processed. The in-between time caused their system to auto-create a new EIN for that biz, causing a mess that took another 6mo. :/

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Of course if you buy the fastest storage AND best chips you get the benefits, but lots of avg. consumers who can now get insane chip speeds don't do that. They grab the 500GB SSD & plug in a SSD that does 1/3rd-1/4th that internal speed, not realizing how backwards that is.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Last 10yrs we had a huge boost in storage speed & cost/GB but now chips are having their moment in a big way & we are upside down again in terms of what people are used to. We were upgrading processing to catch up to read/write speeds but investment focus has to pivot.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: I've said it few times over last few yrs but IMO there should be more talk about where bottlenecks now are. IMO it is storage not chips, & far too many video pros will upgrade systems but still plug in a T5. Even 1000mb/s won't cut it if you want to feel speed of these new chips.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: M1 Ultra & what we'll likely see in benchmarks (after what M1 Max already provided) will prove that for MANY in post-prod, chips are far outpacing what's needed for a large chunk of Apple's customer base. It's brought upper-class+ speed to middle-class customers.

tweet: @TaylorHoliday Sounds like we're saying the same thing I guess. For small biz that front end AOV = big deal & buys you time while you shore up other angles. I don't "worry" about AOV much, but I try to design all the store logic around it. Single item orders w/such high CPM = death right now.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @MiloOutdoorEcom @Gil_RunDMG @andrewfoxwell I figure if I largely saturate at higher freq the same 30d RT buckets i used with conv. but with Traffic LPV or Link Click instead, then I can let them go, and w/exclu at TOF out, I want as little Pixel based delivery optimization  competition as possible. 🤷🏻‍♂️

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Thanks for listening... no idea if this is helpful or not, and so much more to say that would fill in context, but I want filmmakers to have a sustainable pathway, and the options only seem to be shrinking. We'll all figure it out, but we have to be willing to pivot/change.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: If you see your next movie release as one in a hopeful long line of others, then it's not about launching a movie, it's about launching a business of some sort. How does your previous work benefit the new? At some point things have to compound. You can't start over w/each movie.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: What I'm talking about won't work for everyone. Some have no interest at all, and many don't have their businesses or financing setup in a way that makes it possible, but it's what's working for me as I help try to build models that work for others and myself...

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Running Conversion Ads & selling a movie direct has actually become the best way for me to push off-site digital sales believe it or not. I say no to anyone looking for video view ads or link clicks or whatever else. I can't look them in the face, spend it, & know I'm helping.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: None of this is a silver bullet. It's hard. It takes longterm focus. You can't sell your 5 movies off to 3 places either, & if you sign w/ppl you need to try to maintain in contract your ability to sell your own movies so long as it's in your site/system. Sign & pray won't work.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Why did direct digital matter? All of a sudden you're running Ads to people you can't ship to. The globe is open. You're running Ads to ppl in Australia from your bedroom & don't need to take that tiny $3k that distrib is offering to own the movie over there. New world.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: It also allowed digital packing, and if it works, a way to plug your next movie in later on. It's not for everyone, it's for those who wish to support you that way. Tried this 10yr ago but world wasn't ready. Only worked a little. Ad tech wasn't what it is now.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Direct digital was next piece of the puzzle, & still a huge frontier that almost no company has solved. I figured out my own system to use that's less than perfect, but it allowed simple Shopify checkout w/streaming on the other end in a library format. Needs improvement.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: You can't pay for those thousands who saw the Ad today but didn't buy/rent with the $2.50 your $4.99 rental gets you, with a 3month+ delay in payment + distrib % loss. Sorry.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Waste in advertising is inevitable. Ppl see something & say it looks great but forget. You'll inevitably reach many who engage but don't rent/buy, so paying for as much of the waste as you can is critical, otherwise you blow your $ in a month, hope for a pop, then party IS over.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: The real strength came for those who had multiple movies they owned, where the newest movie brought people in but then people left w/2+ or packs, which in high CPM environment is becoming so important. Higher checkout = that much more awareness on top that's paid for.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Those who buy direct help offset awareness cost for those who inevitably buy/rent digital, which is a growing piece of whole pie. If they want to go there, they know where to go, you just need to profitably tell them 1) what the movie is and 2) where it is & keep Ads pumping

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: It wasn't about everyone buying it that way, it was about finding those who would & using rotation of rev to pay for the ongoing awareness you get while running Ads of that sort. That's the game. How do we pay for the awareness ongoing that tends to = off-site digital sales?

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: So party over? Nah, but pathway is narrower than ever before imo. With streaming blowing up, I dove into e-com & encouraged ppl to dig in on what everyone left for dead, physical items, DVD/Blu-ray, ramped up quick/dirty Shopify stores, & begged ppl to listen & try.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: People still dump tons of $ into new VOD release knowing full well they can barely see a report for months & if you can see it, you can't attribute anything + the check is delayed 3mnth+ so cashflow machine is broken for most indies. Can't keep faucet on even IF it's working...

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: CPMs are simply too high nowadays across the board for the # of ppl who can see a simple awareness Ad per $, even well targeted, to convert enough digital buys/rentals & be profitable. You need 2010 CPMs & double digit conversion % in places you can't even track/optimize around.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: You simply can't spend awareness $ effectively & get the required financial pop on various popular platforms in a profitable way (Outside of some free/paid PR luck). I did it for theatricals so know what it's like to spend $ like you're trying to ricochet bullets 4x. It's stupid.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: It's become a total race to the bottom where eyeballs are king, margins are gone, and a few gatekeepers hold all the keys. Musicians know this game already. Bringing an e-com type focus to film a few years ago was all I could think of to help, w/Ads being the REAL overall issue.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: Save a handful of approaches/deals, it's hard for me to see any financial pathway forward for filmmakers making movies of a certain size outside of them owning their movies and having a direct connection with their audience/fans/data, & compounding $ movie to movie.

name: Kyle Prohaska

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @lboy100 @RyanMacfarlan11 @mrahmey @andrewfoxwell **You won't run into this issue if the BM you need to connect and the FB page owned by that BM also *owns the Pixel, but if you're using a Pixel shared to that BM, it won't show up in those initial steps.**

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @lboy100 @RyanMacfarlan11 @mrahmey @andrewfoxwell Then once you get fully through the steps and can get to the actual settings area post-setup, you'll see the proper/full list of Pixels that you should've seen during the multi-step process, select the one you need. Maddening, but that's how this works at the moment.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @lboy100 @RyanMacfarlan11 @mrahmey @andrewfoxwell So when you get to the Pixel step, you might notice a Pixel that SHOULD definitely be there... isn't. To combat this and get things connected, create a dummy Pixel in the connected BM you don't plan to use at all, just to select one through the steps...

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @lboy100 @RyanMacfarlan11 @mrahmey @andrewfoxwell The person setting it up has to be admin of the BM you connect after adding yourself, then the page has to be OWNED inside that BM. Then there's the Pixel, which doesn't have to be owned inside that BM but the Steps they put you through make it *look* like it has to be...

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @lboy100 @RyanMacfarlan11 @mrahmey @andrewfoxwell There's a catch with this though that you'll run into if the person, BM, Page, Pixel, etc. isn't under the same roof. It's a huge headache and depending on how things are structured BTS it's a bit of a nightmare.

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
tweet: @LabSplice Yes. Individually though we fail to teach kids how to handle $ bc we don't know either. Economics class they play a game & have ppl pick stocks, which is largely idiotic, unhelpful, & can teach bad habit vs. showing them what happens if they put 100/mo into an index at 17.

name: Kyle Prohaska

tweet: @lettershome So really it's a marketing "hey you want 12K... well here you go" but it's REALLY a "hey you want way way better 4K or 8K with improved color science and frame rates and other stuff... well here you go!"

name: Kyle Prohaska
description: Filmmaker. Editor. Designer. Marketer. Creative Swiss Army knife for Cos/Orgs/Indies. Lover of Tacos & Tequila #actuallyautistic
